description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking to expand your skills and enhance your career to include providing Complex Clinical Care or do you already have Complex Care experience?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apollo Home Healthcare is seeking an experienced Support Worker to support a young gentleman with complex care needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dedicated and compassionate Support Worker who are passionate about their job, enjoy delivering one to one support and who can build positive relationships with our service users and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service user is currently residing in a respite establishment in Cheshire, and he needs a fantastic team in place to get him home to his family. All shadowing is held at the respite centre in Cheshire which you will be required to attend.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He is a sociable guy who likes to spend quality time with family and friends at his home and enjoys getting out and about in the community and having a laugh and banter with his friends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Football is a big part of his life; he has been playing since he was young and is a massive Manchester United fan, he loves to attend Old Trafford and watch the game.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He has many other hobbies and interests which include, watching several TV series and films, men’s fashion, trips out and socialising with friends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drivers are essential for this role and must be confident in driving an adapted vehicle as this gentleman is looking for someone to get him out into the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* 6 months previous care experience&lt;br /&gt;* Medication Administration&lt;br /&gt;* Personal Care&lt;br /&gt;* Moving and Handling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Tracheostomy Care&lt;br /&gt;* Ventilation Management&lt;br /&gt;* Oral Suctioning&lt;br /&gt;* Spinal Injury Awareness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Monday – Sunday Days and Nights 08:00 – 20:00 &amp; 20:00 – 08:00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and really making an impact on his day to day life. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why work for Apollo Home Healthcare?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We specialise in the provision of highly complex clinical care services delivered in the homes of service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate about delivering the highest standard of care and we recognise that our Nurses, Healthcare Assistants and Support Workers are integral to doing this. In return for your hard work and dedication you will receive:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible hours to suit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirmed rotas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent rates of pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full clinical training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to work with other service users in the area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ongoing professional training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need key workers on the front line supporting our service users in the fight against the COVID-19 Pandemic.&lt;/p&gt;
